## Component Conversion Patterns

### 1. React Function Component → Svelte Component

**React:**

```jsx
function Counter({ initialCount = 0 }) {
    const [count, setCount] = useState(initialCount);

    return (
        <div>
            <p>Count: {count}</p>
            <button onClick={() => setCount(count + 1)}>Increment</button>
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Svelte 5 (runes):**

```svelte
<!-- Counter.svelte -->
<script>
    // $props() replaces function arguments / React props
    let { initialCount = 0 } = $props();

    // $state() replaces useState()
    let count = $state(initialCount);
</script>

<div>
    <p>Count: {count}</p>
    <!-- onclick (lowercase) replaces onClick -->
    <button onclick={() => count++}>Increment</button>
</div>
```

---

### 2. Inertia Page Component (Receives Laravel Props)

**React:**

```jsx
export default function ProductsIndex({ products }) {
    return (
        <div>
            {products.map(p => <ProductCard key={p.id} product={p} />)}
        </div>
    );
}
```

**Svelte:**

```svelte
<!-- resources/js/Pages/Products/Index.svelte -->
<script>
    import ProductCard from '@/Components/ProductCard.svelte';

    // Props from Laravel controller arrive via $props()
    let { products } = $props();
</script>

<div>
    {#each products as product (product.id)}
        <ProductCard {product} />
    {/each}
</div>
```

Laravel controller:

```php
public function index(): \Inertia\Response
{
    return Inertia::render('Products/Index', [
        'products' => Product::all(),
    ]);
}
```

