## State Management Mapping

| React | Svelte 5 (runes) |
|-------|-----------------|
| `useState(value)` | `let x = $state(value)` |
| `useState([])` | `let arr = $state([])` |
| `useState({})` | `let obj = $state({})` |
| `useMemo(fn, [deps])` | `let x = $derived(expression)` |
| `useEffect(fn, [])` | `$effect(() => { ... })` (runs after mount) |
| `useEffect(fn, [dep])` | `$effect(() => { dep; ... })` (auto-tracks) |
| `useCallback(fn, [])` | Plain function (no memoization needed) |
| `useRef(null)` | `let el = $state(null)` + `bind:this={el}` |

### $state — Reactive Variables

```js
// React
const [count, setCount] = useState(0);
setCount(count + 1);

// Svelte 5
let count = $state(0);
count++; // direct mutation triggers reactivity
```

> Svelte 5 allows direct mutation of `$state` variables. No setter function needed.

### $derived — Computed Values

```js
// React
const total = useMemo(() => items.reduce((s, i) => s + i.price, 0), [items]);

// Svelte 5
let items = $state([]);
let total = $derived(items.reduce((s, i) => s + i.price, 0));
```

### $effect — Side Effects

```js
// React
useEffect(() => {
    document.title = `Count: ${count}`;
}, [count]);

// Svelte 5 — automatically tracks any $state read inside
$effect(() => {
    document.title = `Count: ${count}`;
});
```

> `$effect` runs after the DOM updates. It auto-tracks reactive dependencies — no dependency array needed.

