## Data Fetching

### Page Data — From Laravel Controller

```svelte
<script>
    // Data arrives as Svelte props from Inertia — no fetch needed
    let { products } = $props();
</script>
```

### Mutations — Inertia useForm

**React:**

```jsx
const { data, setData, post, processing, errors } = useForm({ name: '' });
```

**Svelte:**

```svelte
<script>
    import { useForm } from '@inertiajs/svelte';

    const form = useForm({ name: '' });

    function submit(e) {
        e.preventDefault();
        form.post(route('products.store'));
    }
</script>

<form onsubmit={submit}>
    <input bind:value={$form.name} type="text" />
    {#if $form.errors.name}
        <p>{$form.errors.name}</p>
    {/if}
    <button disabled={$form.processing}>Save</button>
</form>
```

> In Svelte, `useForm` returns a Svelte store. Access its values with `$form.name`, `$form.errors`, etc.

